				\begin{document}$$b(i) = \mathop {{{\mathrm{min}}}}\limits_{m \ne k} d(i,m).$$\end{document}The cluster m for which this minimum is obtained is called the neighbouring cluster of Xi. If the number of clusters Nk is >1, we can define the silhouette coefficient s(i) for the sample Xi by6s(i)=b(i)-a(i)max{a(i),b(i)}=1-a(i)∕b(i),ifa(i)<b(i)0,ifa(i)=b(i)b(i)∕a(i)-1,ifa(i)>b(i).\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
